Item Name: SAVAGE 110 ULTRALITE ELITE  300 PRC 3 RND 20'' BARREL
Web Item Name: Savage 110 Ultralite Elite Rifle 300 PRC 3rd Capacity 20'' Threaded Black Barrel Gray Synthetic Stock
Web Item Description:
Savage is taking innovation and accuracy to new heights at faster speeds with the 110 Ultralite Elite. With its exclusive Proof Research carbon fiber wrapped stainless steel barrel and MDT HNT26 folding carbon fiber stock the 110 Ultralite Elite can achieve lighter weights for higher altitude hunts and longer treks for big game. Savage® teamed up with PROOF Research® to craft a barrel specific for a purpose driven firearm. At ~5 pounds the 110 Ultralite is designed to combat elevation and elements while maintaining the performance of a factory blueprinted Savage 110 action.

FEATURES

  • PROOF Research Carbon Fiber Wrapped Stainless Steel Barrel 
  • Threaded muzzle - 5/8x24
  • MDT HNT26 Chassis with carbon fiber forend pistol grip and buttstock
  • Gun Metal Grey Cerakote finish on the Magnesium center section
  • Foam-filled carbon buttstock 
  • Adjustable LOP and comb height. Includes four 1/4" LOP spacers
  • Integrated ARCA rail
  • Omniport muzzle brake
  • Lightweight Stainless Steel Receiver with Blackout Cerakote finish
  • Diamond Fluted Bolt coated with Blackout Cerakote
  • Carbon Fiber Bolt Knob
  • Threaded bolt handle (5/16x24) 
  • Drilled & Tapped Receiver (8-40)
  • One piece 20MOA picatinny scope rail
  • Low profile AICS detachable box magazine

Web Item Name: CMMG Defcan 556 Direct Thread Suppressor 5.56 1-3/8x24 Black with 1/2x28 Muzzle Brake
Web Item Description:
The DefCan-556 is a full-auto-rated 5.56mm suppressor that combines robust build quality with remarkable sound reduction. 3D Metal printed Inconel construction delivers durability and a high heat tolerance.
Attachment is easy using the included ZEROED SVD Muzzle Brake or a mil-spec A2 flash hider slide the DEFCAN over the muzzle device 

HUB Compatible
New suppressor mounts and muzzle devices are always on the horizon. Whether your muzzle device needs might change or you just like the looks of something else in the future your DEFCAN will be up for anything new. Threaded with the industry standard 1-3/8x24 HUB system switching to a different QD mounting system is as easy as unscrewing the SVD/A2 mount and attaching your preferred HUB mount.

Includes:

  • Suppressor
  • ZEROED SVD Muzzle Brake 5.56mm 1/2-28
  • Muzzle device shims
  • Thread locker

Item Name: Daniel Defense Suppressor SoundGuard SG-556 1/2-28 BLK
Web Item Name: Daniel Defense SG-556 SoundGuard 1/2-28 Thread - Black
Web Item Description:
Daniel SoundGuard Powered by KGM Suppressors utilize cutting-edge gas-flow dynamics that eliminate over-gassing and direct most gasses forward not back in a shooter’s face. So you experience less toxic gas blowback and can concentrate on putting more shots on target. State-of-the-art KGM technology significantly lowers impulse noise levels protecting against hearing loss while a patent-pending baffle stack and proprietary coating on internal parts reduce a firearm’s flash signature to virtually zero. Patent-pending gas-flow pathing stabilizes rounds to ensure extreme accuracy with minimal point-of-impact shift.

The SG-556 is compatible with .223 and 5.56mm caliber firearms and is constructed of lightweight but extremely durable stainless steel so you don’t have to baby it and it won’t weigh down your barrel. It attaches/detaches in seconds via an included adapter utilizing the HUB standard 1.375-24 UNS which provides secure attachment while adding minimal length and allowing for the use of a variety of other muzzle attachments. Every SG-556 suppressor is stamped with the Daniel name which means it’s backed with a 100% Satisfaction Guarantee.

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS:

  • Weight: 22 oz
  • Length: 7"
  • Diameter: 1.75"
  • Materials: Stainless Steel Baffle Stack and Tube
  • Finish: Black High-Temp Cerakote
  • Thread Pitch: 1/2x28
  • Full Auto Rated!

Item Name: Lantac M-SPEC 22S 22LR Suppressor - Includes 1/2x28 DT Hub and Plan B Hub
Web Item Name: Lantac M-SPEC 22S Suppressor .22 LR with 1/2x28 DT Hub and Plan B Hub
Web Item Description:
The M-SPEC22S is a Patent Pending 22LR caliber suppressor precision machined from aerospace grade 7075-T6 Aluminum and designed to shoot .22LR 17HMR & 22WMR caliber ammunition. Its unique design allows for mounting to either a PlanB adapter or direct thread 1/2-28 UNEF adapter. Each of the five baffles can be removed for easy cleaning and enable length configuration with varying sound suppression levels.

Each suppressor comes as standard with two  adapter options that feature a 1/2-28 UNEF direct thread and a Plan B muzzle device mount.

Machined from 17-4 PH Stainless Steel in H900 condition they can both be fitted using a standard Armorers wrench / Castle Nut tool.

Key Features:

  • Modular baffle design
  • Easy disassembly & cleaning
  • 1/2-28 direct thread & PlanB adapter mounts included.
  • Certified aerospace grade materials for full traceability.
  • Type III hardcoat anodized to MIL-A-8625 standard.
  • Larger baffle volume for improved noise suppression.
  • 17-4 Stainless Steel mounting adapters for improved corrosion resistance and lifespan.
  • Fits 22LR Rifles and Handguns (with red dot sight fitted).
  • 109dB in optimum configuration (22LR Subsonic).
  • Made in the USA.

Item Name: THREAD-ON SOUND SUPPRESSOR  22LR/22MAG/17HMR  1/2-28  SS BAFFLE  BLK
Web Item Name: SureFire SF Ryder 22-S  Suppressor .22 LR/.22 WMR/.17 HMR Direct Thread 1/2-28 Stainless Steel Black
Web Item Description:
The SF Ryder 22-S is a lightweight thread-on suppressor optimized for .17 HMR .22LR and .22 Mag rimfire pistols and rifles. Built to exacting standards like our SOCOM Fast-Attach® suppressors it features a patented aluminum body with rounded ends and flutes for reduced weight without sacrificing strength. Weighing just over 5 ounces and measuring only 5.4 inches long the SF Ryder 22-S minimizes effects on weapon weight and maneuverability. Our proprietary heat-treated stainless steel baffles provide superior sound attenuation and tremendous durability even during full-auto use. Our proprietary internal design reduces carbon buildup and keeps the suppressor clean longer. It’s also easy to disassemble clean and reassemble. The SF Ryder 22-S is simply the best thread-on suppressor available for .17 HMR and .22 shooters.

Specifications:

  • Patented body design has rounded ends and flutes to reduce weight with no sacrifice in strength
  • Patented pig-nose baffles provide superior sound attenuation
  • Stainless steel baffles enable easy cleaning and help prevent gas/ particle erosion
  • Indexed baffles are numbered for ease of reassembly; built-in spacers help reduce carbon buildup between baffles
  • Single-point cut 1/2-28 threads provide secure attachment
  • Includes assembly/disassembly tool and spud-extension tool for easy baffle-stack removal
  • Durable construction delivers long service life
  • Proudly designed and manufactured in the U.S.A.

Item Name: Surefire Suppressor 2nd Gen 5.56 - 300 WM - Black
Web Item Name: Surefire 2nd Gen Fast Attach SOCOM300-SPS Suppressor 5.56 - 300 WM - Stainless Steel Black
Web Item Description:
The SureFire SOCOM300-SPS is the answer for .300 BLK/Whisper (7.62 x 35) subsonic and supersonic ammo users seeking superior levels of sound attenuation from a precision-built suppressor. It’s also very capable in 5.56 mm and 300 WM applications. The SPS features highly specialized V-shaped baffles that promote the utmost in sound suppression for subsonic ammunition while virtually eliminating first-round flash and dust signatures. Constructed of Inconel alloy and stainless steel and CNC laser-welded it’s stealthy without sacrificing an ounce of strength. Go ahead. Make it rain.

Specifications:

 

  • The quietest suppressor in the SureFire family optimized for .300 BLK carbines with 10-inch or shorter barrels
  • Oversized yet precision machined bore diameter decreases the baffle strike probability from unstable projectiles
  • 7.9-inch overall length optimized for superior signature reduction
  • Baffles are specifically designed and optimized for subsonic ammunition
  • Eliminates first-round flash a phenomenon common in most suppressors
  • Suppresses visible flash by up to 99.5%
  • Tight tolerances and precision bore concentricity result in superior accuracy
  • Cutting-edge internal venting reduces back pressure cyclic rate and gas blowback to significantly reduce operating temperatures
  • Compatible with the SureFire array of Fast-Attach® mounting adapters (flash hiders compensators and WARCOMPS)
  • Fast-Attach® design allows fast secure easy attachment and removal without tools
  • All SOCOM300-SPS suppressors are test-fired to verify sub-1 MOA group size and point-of-impact shift
  • Every SureFire SOCOM Series suppressor comes with a FirstSpear™ MOLLE pouch and cleaning brush
  • Durable construction delivers a long service life
  • Proudly designed and manufactured in the U.S.A.
  • CALIBER: 7.62 mm / .308 / .300 Blackout

Item Name: Surefire Suppressor End Mount Titanium 7.62mm/308
Web Item Name: Surefire End Mount SOCOM762-Ti2 Rifle Suppressor 7.62mm Titanium Black
Web Item Description:
The SOCOM762-Ti2 enhances Surefire’s exceptional titanium suppressor line by providing the ultimate lightweight suppressor for 7.62 mm and .308-caliber bolt-action rifles. We designed it to exceed military sniper rifle suppressor specifications making it the ideal lightweight suppressor for hunters and long-range precision shooters alike. SureFire's strict manufacturing tolerances and exacting attention to bore concentricity and suppressor alignment result in tremendous accuracy. Constructed primarily of titanium the SOCOM762-Ti2 weighs a mere 11 ounces while maintaining our strictest durability standards so you won't even feel it at the end of your barrel. Inside its Direct Metal Laser Sintered V-shaped titanium baffle stack significantly provides an unprecedented level of baffle alignment and structural integrity. The SOCOM762-Ti2 attenuates the muzzle report significantly and our internal venting technology evenly distributes thermodynamic gases greatly reducing pressure impulse effects on the projectile as it clears the muzzle. The SOCOM762-Ti2 is a durable 7.62/.308 titanium suppressor without equal.

Item Name: SMR MRAD Fixed Stock 300 PRC 26'' Fluted W (1) 10RND MAGS BLACK
Web Item Name: Barrett SMR MRAD Fixed Stock Rifle .300 PRC 10rd Magazine(1) 26'' Fluted Barrel Black Finish
Web Item Description:
Designed with both precision and modularity in mind the MRAD is equally at home on the range or on duty.

A new addition to the award-winning MRAD product line the Single Mission Rifle (SMR).
The new MRAD SMR features the same performance of the regular MRAD along with .75 MOA accuracy but in a simplified package utilizing 90% parts commonality with the standard MRAD configuration.

The Single Mission Rifle name comes from the fact that the rifle is set from the factory in only one caliber unlike the interchangeable barrel ability of the standard MRAD. The primary distinction of the SMR is the free float barrel which is held in the upper receiver with a standard barrel nut. Additionally the non-folding stock is fixed with a vertically adjustable cheek piece and separate spacers for length of pull adjustment. These changes lead to a slimmer lighter overall rifle; trimming nearly 2 ½ lbs. off the weight and 1 inch off the overall length of the standard MRAD rifle.

Features:

  • Caliber: 300 PRC
  • Operation: Bolt Action Repeater
  • Barrel Length: 26” (660 mm)
  • Twist Rate: 1 : 8” (200 mm)
  • Overall Length: 48.5” (1232 mm)
  • Weight: 12.3 lbs (5.6 kg)
  • Mag. Capacity: 10
  • Rail Length/MOA: 21.75” (553 mm) 10 Mil

The USSOCOM Advanced Sniper Rifle (ASR) and U.S. Army Precision Sniper Rifle (PSR) contract winner.

The MK 22 defines a new class of long-range rifles by providing even greater capability within the MRAD rifle platform. With unfailing precision and Sub-MOA performance this bolt action sniper rifle adapts to a variety of user needs by converting between 7.62 x 51mm 300 NM and 338 NM calibers. The aluminum chassis features a folding stock with adjustable length of pull and cheek piece M-LOK® attachment system 10 mil rail and suppressor capable muzzle brake.

Item Name: B&T Titanium 762 Rotex Compact W/ SF Adapter Suppressor
Web Item Name: B&T Print-X Rotex 762 TI Compact Suppressor 7.62x51 NATO Grey w/SF HUB Adapter
Web Item Description:
The Rotex 762 Compact Titanium is the ideal choice when weight savings is priority number one. Forty-percent lighter than its 718 Inconel brethren the Rotex Tioffers substantial weight savings yet maintains the same high performance you’ve come to expect from B&T's Rotex line of suppressors inclusive of exceptional soundsuppression capabilities extreme durability and longevity all while providing industry leading sound and flash reduction. The Rotex Ti is barely there providingminimal deviation in point of aim/point of impact. Given the nature of titanium we recommend use on platforms that see lower-volume firing schedules that are moreprecision-oriented such as SPRs and bolt-action rifles. The compact model is great choice for those seeking a balance between sound and signature reduction andoverall length. The modular Lunar 9 suppressor offers two shooting configurations the ultra-quiet full-length 7” configuration and the ultra-compact 4.7” configuration. Crafted from Type III hard-coat anodized 7075 Aluminum and a 17-4 Stainless Steel blast baffle the Gemtech Lunar 9 suppressor is lightweight full-auto rated for 9mm and capable of handling as many rounds as you are.

The Gemtech® Lunar® 9 suppressor features an innovative baffle design that allows it to be converted from a longer 7" suppressor to a shorter 4.7" suppressor while still being hearing-safe. The new GEMTECH Lunar 9 suppressor is compatible with a variety of threaded barrel pistols carbines and rifles chambered for 9mm and subsonic 300 BLK that are currently on the market.

Specifications:

  • Caliber: 9MM 300BLK
  • Sound Tested: 129dBC LONG / 135dBC SHORT Glock® 17 Gen 4 | 136 dBC LONG BCM® Standard 9 300BLK
  • Diameter: 1.4"

  • Mount Type: Ships with 1/2 x 28 LID assembly. Compatible with all GM®-9 mounting options
  • Tube Material: 7075 Aluminum
  • Full Auto Rated: Yes
  • Tube Finish: Matte BLK Type III Hard Coat Anodize

Item Name: 1875 OUTLAW 7 Inch 45LC
Web Item Name: 1875 OUTLAW 7 Inch 45LC
Web Item Description:
Designed to compete with Colt's 1873 single-action the 1875 Remington revolver has a similar yet distinctive look all its own. Around 25000 of these sleek six-shooters were turned out from1875-1889 and were held in high esteem by many Westerners including none other than the notorious outlaw Frank James who praised its handling capabilities as did noted 1880sTexas Ranger Bill McDonald. It was also the choice of the U.S. Department of the Interior who purchased several hundred in 1883 as an issue sidearm to Indian police on frontier reservations. Cimarron's 1875 Outlaw is available in either the 5 1/2-inch or the 7 1/2-inch barrel lengths. Calibers offered are .357 Magnum/.38 Special .44 WCF or .45 Colt (7 1/2-inch is also offered in .45 Colt/.45 ACP with dual cylinders) The '75 Outlaw comes in Standard Blue with a color case hardened frame and hammer. Cimarron's 1875 Model has captured the looks and feel of this frontier smokewagon that has also been catching on with today's silver screen cowhands and has seen use in such popular westerns as Open Range Broken Trail and 3:10 To Yuma. The Outlaw is a true Western classic!

Features:

  • Caliber: .45 COLT
  • Barrel Length: 7 1/2 in.
  • Style: 1875 Outlaw
  • Frame: Standard Blue
  • Finish: Standard Blue
  • Grip: 1 Piece Walnut
  • Overall Length: No
  • Weight: 2.6 Lbs.

Item Name: 1873 SADDLE RIFLE 18 Inch 357
Web Item Name: 1873 SADDLE RIFLE 18 Inch 357
Web Item Description:
Arguably the most famous rifle of the Old West Winchester's first centerfire arm was manufactured from 1873-1919 with more than 541000 turned out before 1900. A frontier favorite since its debut this lever-action rifle was produced in a number of variations from short Trapper models and carbines to short and extra-long barreled rifles. A few short years after the 1873 rifle was introduced it was often teamed with the famed 1873 Peacemaker and other sixguns that had been chambered for the '73's .44-40 (.44WCF) .38-40 (.38 WCF) and .32-20 (.32 WCF) ammunition. The premier choice of the post-1874 Texas Rangers this slab-sided saddle rifle was also favored by such well-known Westerners as Pat Garrett William F. Cody Montana Rancher Granville Stuart and outlaws Butch Cassidy Belle Starr and Billy the Kid. Cimarron offers more variations than any other company from plain to fully engraved with hand-checkered pistol-gripped stocks and in barrel lengths that run from a short 16 inches to a full 30 inches long. Calibers offered are .32-20 38 Special/.357 Magnum 38/40 .44 Special/.44 Magnum .44-40 and .45 Colt. Cimarron's '73s come in Standard Blue Charcoal Blue or Original Finish and with straight walnut stocks or collector quality hand-checkered deluxe models with the pistol grip stock. From Saddle Ring Carbine to Long Range Sporting Rifle like the originals Cimarron's 1873 lever guns are considered the best!

  • Caliber: 357/38 Spl.
  • Barrel Length: 18 in. Octagon
  • Style: Saddle Rifle
  • Capacity: 10+1
  • Frame: Color Case Hardened
  • Finish: Standard Blue
  • Grip: Walnut
  • Overall Length: No
  • Weight: 8 Lbs.

Web Item Name: Tisas PX-9 2.0 Duty Comp Handgun 9mm Luger 18rd(1)&20rd(1) Magazines 4.1'' Barrel Optic Ready
Web Item Description:
The PX-9 Duty Comp is the next evolution of the proven PX-9 series. Now equipped with a match-grade barrel and a compensator port it offers exceptional recoil control for faster follow-up shots. The slide features aggressive serrations and machined cuts for reduced weight and enhanced grip. Designed with both duty and competition in mind it utilizes high-capacity P226-pattern magazines and includes a factory RMR optic cut for co-witnessing with standard sights.

Ambidextrous controls and reversible aluminum magazine release make it ideal for left- or right-handed shooters. With 27 ergonomic grip configurations upgraded aluminum trigger take-down lever and magwell this striker-fired 9mm delivers high-performance features at an unmatched value.

Notable Features:

  • Aggressive Machined Slide Cuts for Weight Reduction & Grip

  • Match-Grade Barrel with Integrated Compensator Port

  • Aluminum Flat-Faced Trigger with Tactile Reset

  • Aluminum Extended Magwell Take-Down Lever and Magazine Catch

  • Ambidextrous Slide Stop & Optional Thumb Safety

  • Co-Witness Sight Height (Glock® Pattern)

  • RMR Optic Cut with Cover Plate Installed

  • 226 Pattern Magazines – 18rd & 20rd Included

  • 27 Grip Configuration Options with Interchangeable Panels & Backstraps

  • Tenifer QPQ Finish for Corrosion and Wear Resistance

  • Striker Status & Loaded Chamber Indicators

  • 1-Year Warranty / Lifetime Service Plan

The slick black chromate finish and checked polymer grips are complimented with Browning® dovetail military type sights a ring hammer extended ambidextrous safety and period correct lanyard loop.

Inglis pistols come standard in a polymer lockable hard case two magazines cleaning kit trigger lock and instruction manual.

Caliber: 9mm Luger

Barrel Length: 4.7" 1:10RH Twist Button Rifled

Barrel Material/Finish: 4140 Forged & Machined Hard Chrome Finish

Frame Material: Forged 4140 Carbon Steel

Slide Material: Forged 4140 Carbon Steel

Grips: Black Checkered Ploymer

Trigger: Approx. 7lb

Finish: Black Chromate Over Electroless Nickel

Front Sight: Black Browning® Dovetail Pattern

Rear Sight: Black Browning® Dovetail Pattern

Item Name: Tisas 1911 DUTY B9R DS 9MM 5'' BLK Cerakote Ti Firing Pin Double Stack Rail
Web Item Name: Tisas 1911 Duty B9R Double Stack Handgun 9mm Luger 17rd Magazine 5'' Barrel  Black Cerakote RMS/c Optic
Web Item Description:
The Tisas 1911 Duty B9R Double Stack 1911 takes the iconic 1911 platform to the next level offering cutting-edge performance at an unbeatable value. Building on the success of last year’s models Tisas USA is doubling down on their commitment to the 1911 double-stack market by introducing a host of new upgrades all while keeping the price point accessible. This full-sized semi-automatic handgun is designed for shooters who demand both power and precision without compromising on quality.

Key Features:

  • High-Capacity Double-Stack Magazine: The B9R boasts a 17+1 round capacity offering significant firepower in a slim ergonomic package making it ideal for duty use or personal defense.
  • Bushing-Less Bull Barrel: Both the Duty and Carry models have been upgraded to a bushing-less style bull barrel featuring a precision-machined target crown. Paired with a full-length guide rod this design improves both accuracy and recoil management for a smoother shooting experience.
  • RMSc/K Slide Cuts for Optics: The B9R is optic-ready with RMSc/K slide cuts that allow direct mounting of a variety of modern red-dot sights (RDS). This feature provides a lower 1/3 co-witness with the included standard-height sights ensuring fast precise target acquisition.
  • Durable Steel Frame & Slide: The all-steel construction offers durability and a solid shooting platform while the textured polymer grips ensure a secure hold under any conditions.
  • Universal Accessory Rail: A newly designed universal type accessory rail on the frame accepts popular weapon lights and it standardizes holster fitment with other 1911 double-stack models making it easier to customize and integrate with your preferred gear.
  • Ambidextrous Safety: The ambidextrous safety allows for quick intuitive manipulation making it ideal for both left- and right-handed shooters.
  • Smooth Trigger & Hammer: A crisp smooth trigger and a commander-style hammer ensure precise controlled shots even in high-stress situations.

Designed for everyday carry and self-defense this striker-fired 9mm balances concealability with high-capacity performance. With 27 grip configuration options and ergonomic controls it’s comfortable for every hand size and shooting style.

Item Name: BANISH 12 SUPPRESSOR BLACK
Web Item Name: Banish 12 Choke Mounted Shotgun Suppressor Titanium Black
Web Item Description:
Shotguns are among the most versatile and popular firearms in the hands of today’s sportsmen and women. Unfortunately pre-existing shotgun suppressors really didn’t offer the same degree of performance or utility. Luckily BANISH engineers enjoy a good challenge.  

Enter the BANISH 12. 

A first-of-its-kind shotgun suppressor the BANISH 12 sets a new standard for scattergun performance. Its all-titanium construction is both durable and lightweight – just 17.6 ounces. Paired with a corrosion-resistant Cerakote finish the BANISH 12 promises longevity from the salt-water blinds to the upland fields and turkey woods while maintaining the handling characteristics that shotgunners value. 

Designed to meet the needs of wingshooters the BANISH 12’s unique profile maintains an unobstructed sight picture from the barrel to the bead and to the bird. It attaches securely using mounts specific to your shotgun’s choke tube design for enhanced compatibility and proper alignment. The 12-gauge suppressor also comes with three interchangeable choke tubes – Improved Cylinder Modified and Full – to provide controlled patterns and quiet reports. 

BANISH the noise bring on the birds.

Web Item Description:
Purpose-built with the modern shooter in mind the Performance Center® M&P®15 AXE™ delivers. This fully ambidextrous rifle adapts to changing environments and keeps versatility in mind. The flat trigger design optimizes accuracy potential by mitigating left and right play when pressing the trigger. With the Gemtech® GVAC® system the M&P®15 AXE™ changes the game when it comes to suppressed shooting by mitigating gas blowback maintaining pinpoint accuracy and easily mounting a suppressor with the ETM® flash hider. Reliable durable and the ultimate suppressor host – get the Performance Center® M&P®15 AXE™.

GVAC® Gas system - Reduces gas blow-back when suppressed - compared to a traditional direct-impingement format.

M&P®15 AXE™ “Ambi X Enhancement”- The forged lower receiver features ambi bolt catch magazine catch and safety selector allowing users full firearm manipulation from either strong or support side.

Improved Reliability BCG - Bolt carrier and firing pin feature unique geometry for improved reliability in dusty sandy environments.

  • Gemtech® ETM® Flash hider.
  • GVAC® mid length direct impingement gas system.
  • Midwest Industries Combat M-LOK® Free-Float seven sided handguard.
  • Radian® Raptor™ charging handle.
  • M&P® tactical adjustable folding front and rear sights.
  • Ambidextrous controls.
  • HIPERFIRE® Enhanced Duty Trigger® w/Copper PVD finish.
  • Magpul® DT Carbine adjustable stock.
  • M&P® grip with four interchangeable backstraps.

With the Gemtech® GVAC® system the M&P®15 AXE™ changes the game when it comes to suppressed shooting by mitigating gas blowback maintaining pinpoint accuracy and easily mounting a suppressor with the ETM® flash hider. Reliable durable and the ultimate suppressor host – get the Performance Center® M&P®15 AXE™.

GVAC® Gas system - Reduces gas blow-back when suppressed - compared to a traditional direct-impingement format.

M&P®15 AXE™ “Ambi X Enhancement”- The forged lower receiver features ambi bolt catch magazine catch and safety selector allowing users full firearm manipulation from either strong or support side.

Improved Reliability BCG - Bolt carrier and firing pin feature unique geometry for improved reliability in dusty sandy environments.

  • WEIGHT: 17.5 oz Complete Assembly.
  • OPTICS: 15 MOA rail. 

Other Features:

  • Ambidextrous charging handle positions
  • Left-side cover plate
  • Rear cleaning port access
  • Interchangeable charging handles

Enhancements:

  • Standard 15 MOA milled-in picatinny rail [open sights are visible with this system].
  • Modular Bolt Handle System with long or short options.
  • Updated aesthetics with distinctive side pocketing.
  • Included dust cover for left side charging window.
  • Enlarged ejection port with beveled contours to promote ejection and mitigate “stovepipes” etc.

Item Name: Ruger LC Carbine 10mm Auto 16.25'' Threaded Barel
Web Item Name: Ruger LC Carbine Rifle 10mm Auto 30rd Magazine 16.25'' Threaded Barrel Black
Web Item Description:
Features:

  • Standard model features a threaded barrel reversible side-folding adjustable stock and 30-round magazine.
  • Designed to accept commonly available Glock-pattern full size magazines.*
  • Unique bolt-over-barrel design with the magazine in the grip allows for excellent balance and control.
  • Reversible folding stock and collapsible sights are ideal for storage.
  • The stock features an adjustable length of pull and is designed to allow for stock compatibility with most AR-pattern stocks.
  • A Picatinny rail at the rear of the receiver allows for maximum accessory compatibility.
  • Features a 16.25" alloy steel barrel with .578"-28 threaded barrel with thread protector allowing for the attachment of popular muzzle accessories including muzzle brakes flash hiders and caliber-appropriate suppressors.
  • Impressive ergonomics with ambidextrous manual safety reversible charging handle ergonomic bolt release and extended magazine release.
  • Utilizes Ruger's safe reliable and proven Secure Action fire-control system that combines a protected internal hammer with a bladed-safety trigger. The trigger has a short smooth pull clean break and positive reset.
  • CNC-milled handguard that is Type III hard-coat anodized aluminum for maximum durability with M-LOK accessory attachment slots on seven sides. Multiple QD sling sockets allow for maximum versatility.
  • Ruger Rapid Deploy folding sights are adjustable for windage and elevation and the full length Picatinny rail allows for optic mounting.
  • Safety features include: 1911-style ambidextrous manual safety; an integrated trigger safety; lightweight firing pin; neutrally balanced sear with significant engagement and strong spring tension; and hammer catch to help prevent the hammer from contacting the firing pin unless the trigger is pulled.
  • Also includes: one magazine M-LOK QD sling socket and hex wrenches for disassembly.

* Older Glock magazines that feature only one magazine latch slot may still be used with the LC Carbine but the magazine release button must remain on the left side of the rifle as shipped from the factory. The magazine release button should not be reversed when using this type of magazine as the magazine will not properly lock into the magazine well.

Item Name: HUXWRX FLOW 556k (FDE) Suppressor w/o Muzzle Device
Web Item Name: Huxwrx Flow 556K Suppressor 5.56 FDE w/Out Muzzle Device
Web Item Description:
An innovative multi-caliber suppressor with patented and proven Flow-Through and Torque Lock technology. It is designed to reduce signature without negatively impacting cycling or service life. The FLOW 556k is DMLS printed in 17-4 Stainless. It delivers superior toxic fume exposure mitigation flash reduction sound reduction recoil reduction accuracy and repeatability by its unique Flow-Through helical coil and core deflector design. It is full-auto rated and compatible on 5.56 17 HMR and 5.7 platforms. The integrated GeoFlash Cap geometry effectively mitigates flash as part of its overall signature reduction funtionality.

Compatible with Muzzle Brake-QD 556 and Flash Hider-QD 556.

Item Name: HUXWRX VENTUM 762 Suppressor
Web Item Name: Huxwrx Ventum 762 Suppressor 7.62 with 5/8x24
Web Item Description:
Evolution at its finest—the VENTUM 762 brings HUB compatible Flow-Through technology to the next level. Named for its function this new HUXWRX suppressor makes 5.56 6.5 and 7.62 calibers a “breeze”. With a removeable 3D-printed Grade 5 Titanium core and 17-4 stainless steel suppressor housing the VENTUM 762 is easily serviceable and provides all the benefits of true Flow-Through technology including toxic fume mitigation improved sound performance and excellent repeatability. Full-auto rated and direct thread ready this multi-caliber suppressor is versatile with a detachable GeoFlash cap and comes ready to accept universal HUB and Stiction mounting systems. The universal HUB mounting system will allow adapters such as Xeno KeyMo and ASR plus other approved mounting systems. It is cross-platform functional and ideal for bolt and lever action centerfire submachine gun bullpup and AK platforms.

With the Flow-Through design no significant modifications to the platform or gas system are required to install or operate this suppressor.

Flow-Through technology cycles and redirects expanding gases in a helical pattern away from the bore-line through the front of the suppressor and away from the shooter’s face eyes and lungs.

Ships with a 5/8x24 direct thread adapter.

Item Name: HUXWRX FLOW Range 36 Ti Black
Web Item Name: Huxwrx Flow Range 36 Ti Suppressor 9mm Luger Hub QD Adapter Black
Web Item Description:
The FLOW Range 36 Ti is the ultimate choice for versatility. It's perfect for first-time suppressor buyers or anyone seeking a single all-purpose suppressor. This extremely lightweight multi-caliber suppressor features hybridized Flow-Through technology offering superior performance across various platforms. Its enhanced GeoFlash Cap with extended lugs makes installation and removal hassle-free. The suppressor is fully optimized for pistols rifles PCCs and sub-guns ensuring optimal performance in every application. Crafted from high-quality Grade 5 titanium and fully 3D-printed the FLOW Range 36 Ti is built to last. Its design also incorporates stiction mounting and hub adapter capability further enhancing its versatility. The FLOW Range 36 Ti is fully-auto rated and has no barrel restrictions. No modifications to the platform or gas system are required to install or operate this suppressor.

  • WEIGHT: 8.4oz / 238g — 12oz / 340g with included HUB QD adapter
  • CALIBER: Pistol calibers up to 9mm; Rifle calibers 17 HMR–.338 Lapua .338 arc 8.6 blkout
  • MATERIALS: S Suppressor: Grade 5 Titanium HUB QD adapter: 17-4 Heat Treated Stainless Steel
  • COATINGS: Suppressor: C-Series Cerakote Matte Black (Flat Dark Earth available) HUB QD adapter: DLC/Black Nitride
  • TECHNOLOGY READINESS: TR Level 9 Fully developed in production
  • MOUNTS: Ships with HUB QD adapter; 3-LUG HUB stiction and direct thread adapters available.
  • BARREL LENGTH: No restrictions
  • DURABILITY: Passes 6 cycles of the SOCOM Reliability Stress Test. (1 cycle=8x30 round magazines)
  • MAINTENANCE: Detailed cleaning should be performed every 2000 rounds.

Item Name: Weatherby 307 ALPINE CT 280AI 22'' +2'' Brake 3+1 Bronze Carbon Fiber
Web Item Name: Weatherby 307 Alpine CT .280 Ackley Imp 3rd Capacity 22'' Threaded Barrel w/2'' Bronze Brake Carbon Fiber w/ WYO Brown Sponge Pattern
Web Item Description:
The Alpine CT is built on Weatherby’s newest bolt action rifle platform the Model 307. Meant to complement the historic Mark V and Vanguard lineups the Model 307 action is a 2-lug fully cylindrical action compatible with many aftermarket accessories. Model 307 is designed to accommodate the vast offerings of stocks triggers rails and mounts that exist in today’s marketplace. Weatherby teamed up with PEAK 44 to produce an ultra-light rifle that can own the range and dominate in the field. The PEAK 44 Bastion stock weighs in at 24 ounces and uses a proprietary 3D-Hex recoil pad to reduce the effects of recoil. You’ll also find that the barrels on the Alpine MDT Carbon are shorter than our traditional offerings. The BSF carbon barrel delivers unmatched accuracy and comes with Weatherby’s Accubrake DST (Directional Self-Timing Brake).

Specifications:

  • Caliber: .280 ACKLEY IMPROVED
  • Weight: 6.3lbs.
  • Overall Length: 44“
  • Mag Capacity: 4
  • Barrel Contour: #4 CARBON
  • Barrel Threads: 5/8-24
  • Barrel OAL: 24" (22" barrel + 2" muzzle brake)
  • Twist Rate: 1:9“
  • Length of Pull: 13.5“
  • Drop @ Comb: .49“
  • Monte Carlo: N/A
  • Drop @ Heel: 35“

Item Name: YHM SIDEWINDER M2 9MM SUPPRESSOR 1/2''-28
Web Item Name: YHM 9mm Sidewinder M2 Direct Thread Suppressor 9mm Luger Aluminum/Steel Black 1/2?-28
Web Item Description:
The Sidewinder M2 is user serviceable which allows both the baffle and Nielsen device to be removed for cleaning and maintenance using the provided disassembly tool.
The booster system has been completely redesigned and now uses the industry’s unofficial standard piston. The redesign also includes the ability to swap pistons without the use of tools thanks to a new rear cap. The front cap has been redesigned to allow for better engagement with the takedown tool to make the service process easier.
YHM's Nielsen device enables flawless semi-automatic operation on all relevant host pistols. The Sidewinder M2 has 12 index points that allow you to adjust point of impact while our device remains attached to the host firearm. The average dry sound signature of the Sidewinder M2 9mm when testing to Mil-Std 1474D is 125 dB dry on a Glock G17 using 147gr. FMJ ammo. Shooting the suppressor “wet” will net even quieter results.

  • Caliber: 9mm
  • Weight: 8.8oz./10.2 w/Piston
  • Length: 8.2”/8.35” w/Piston
  • Diameter: 1.375”
  • Construction: Aircraft Quality Aluminum & 17-4 Ph SS
  • Mount: 1/2”-28 RH Piston
  • Decibel Rating: 125 dB
  • Full Auto Rated
  • Can be used on .300 BLK SUBSONIC with a 7.5" or longer barrel.

YHM’s .30 caliber sound suppressor the Resonator® R2 was created to provide the shooting enthusiast with a quiet lightweight and cost effective suppressor. The notched rim and tri-port muzzle on the end cap make it stand out among the crowd. Web Item Description:
This 5.56 NATO suppressor sports new baffle geometry resulting in reduced blowback. Built with the same care quality and attention to detail that has defined the YHM® brand for generations the Fat Cat® was created to provide a compact suppressor with great sound. The Fat Cat® is made from 17-4 stainless steel along with a Cobalt 6blast baffle. The combination of these materials allows the suppressor to be full auto-rated and designed for rigorous use. The overall length measures just 4.5” with the sRx® adapter installed. That’s a full inch shorter than our Turbo K model with its included adapter. The Fat Cat’s larger 1.94” diameter creates more internal volume resulting in a lower more pleasant tone. With an average sound pressure level of 139dB at the muzzle the Fat Cat® is quite the performer for its size. Available in either standard or Cat’s Ass endcap.
The Fat Cat® includes the sRx® 1/2” x 28 QD Adapter Mini sRx® Muzzle Brake (1) YHM-2007 and (1) YHM-2146.

Item Name: Q Erector 22 22 LR MODULAR 1/2-28 MOUNT .99 OD X 7.6 L
Web Item Name: Q Erector .22 LR Modular 1/2-28 Mount .99 OD x 7.6 L
Web Item Description:
The Erector by Q is the definition of modular.

The erector is made up of black hard-coat anodized aircraft grade aluminum baffles a mount and front cap complimented by a heat treated stainless steel blast baffle. Notice there’s no mention of an outer tube.

No outer tube means more internal volume making this silencer so quiet it’s in a class of its own.

It’s not only the quietest .22 silencer it’s also the lightest at only 2.6 oz in its longest configuration. On top of that it’s also the loudest longest and shortest silencer on the market…Wait. What?

Configure this silencer with one baffle or all ten to fit the needs of your host firearm and ammunition. The choice is yours..choose wisely.

Item Name: JK CCX 9 Black Suppressor (Sell with GLUX4350201FRSPBLK)
Web Item Name: JK Armament 105 CCX 9 Black Direct Thread Suppressor 9mm Luger Aluminum
Web Item Description:
The JK 105 CCX 9MM is the first and only 9mm suppressor capable of going from the shooting range to your concealed carry rig! It’s a tool not a toy that’s designed to live on your carry gun for when seconds count and hearing protection isn’t available. The CCX is so compact that it fits many factory holsters and doesn’t impede your sight picture and it’s so lightweight that it runs on 9mm pistols without a booster! JK’s Mission Configurable design lets you choose the length that works best for your gun and your mission.

The CCX is considered a micro ultralight pistol suppressor and is part of our special use line. Half the size and weight of the competition our special use suppressors perform best when run wet.
 

INCLUDES:

(1) JK 105 LT Thread Mount 1/2×28 TPI

(1) JK 105 LT 1.3” Tube

(1) JK 105 LT Tube Extension

(5) JK 105 LT Pistol Baffle

(1) JK 105 LT CCK Flash Reducer End Cap
